1903.00698.description:
  In the extended Nambu--Jona-Lasinio model, the decay widths of the processes $	au 	o [\omega(782), \phi(1020)] K^{-} 
u_{	au}$ were calculated. The intermediate strange quark-antiquark mesons in both the ground and the first radially excited states were taken into account. The meson $K_{1}(1400)$, being a possible candidate for the role of the tetraquark meson, was also taken into account as an intermediate state. The result for the process $	au 	o \omega(782) K^{-} 
u_{	au}$ is in satisfactory agreement with the experimental data. Simultaneously, the result for the decay $	au 	o \phi(1020) K^{-} 
u_{	au}$ is in agreement with the experimental data with precision $1.3 \sigma$.
